</P>
<P>
   CALLENDAR-HOUSE (Tivoli, N.Y.) _ A decade ago, Pierre Moulin and
his partner, Pierre (Peter) LeVec _ the couple known far and wide
as Pierre Deux, as much for their joyous Provencal style as for the
colorful French cottons they sold at their fabric and antiques
emporia _ bought this late-18-century Hudson River house and its 47
acres, and started inviting friends, relatives and strangers for
parties and teas, and concerts in the old emerald-green carriage
house north of the main house. Now, with great regret, Moulin, 72,
has decided to part with Callendar House, and he has spent a mellow
Saturday afternoon recounting the highlights of his decade there.
By Tracie Rozhon.
</P>
