worry, though. He may go Hollywood and he may be shorn, but the
tattoos, the piercings and leather get-ups remain.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FILM: HARRISON FORD &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The David Carusos and Ryan Philippes of the world may come and
go, but Harrison Ford _ now in the fourth decade of his career _ is
definitely built to last. The former carpenter's rugged,
regular-guy appeal has helped him become this century's most
dependable action hero: His movies have pulled in an astonishing $2
billion worldwide. As for his unstudied sense of style _ part
Marlboro Man, part soccer dad-well, ``it's match-the-hatch,'' Ford
says. ``That's a fly fishing term. You try to present the fish with
something that looks most like its natural food. I try to dress for
the circumstance. Think of it as protective coloration.''
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS: TIGER WOODS &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Number one-ranked Tiger Woods, who turned the golf world on its
ear in 1997 when he won the Masters at the age of 21 by a
record-setting 12 strokes, has had a tough act to follow: his own.
Yet he has managed to hold his trademark smile and graciousness
through a string of frustrating near-misses in the past year.
Unlike many pro athletes, Woods has taken on the mantle of role
model willingly and responsibly. This year, his Tiger Woods
Foundation will conduct four golf clinics around the country for
inner-city youths during which Woods himself will help out with the
lessons.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS: TONY BLAIR &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Tony Blair stands in stark contrast to past British prime
ministers, not to mention most of the gray men of British politics.
First, there are his boyish looks at 46 (which he turns next
month). Then, there's his meet-the-people style, an M.O. that's far
more Clintonian than Churchillian. Blair may wear the same classic
British suits as his predecessor John Major, but the cut is more
Savile Row than Marks &AMP; Spencer. While on vacation, the
American-admiring Blair favors jeans the staple of his youth as
lead guitarist in the rock band Ugly Rumours.  &QL;   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _______ &QC;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; (By the Editors of DNR, Fairchild Publications.) &LR;  &QL;
</P>
