<SLUG> BC-SLATE-ADVISORY-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPEEDING-WHILE-SOBER  
 BRADLEY-PHONY-SURGE  
 CLINTON-GUN-SPIN  
 OFF-LINE-RETAILERS 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SLATE, the premier online magazine of politics and culture, is
now available to your readers from The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   Today:
</P>
<P>
   1. BE AS RECKLESS AS YOU WANT ON THE ROADS--JUST DON'T DRINK, by
Steve Chapman
</P>
<P>
   Today, drunken drivers rank as one notch above child molesters
in the popular mind. But when it comes to sober speeders, the
attitude is, Party On!
</P>
<P>
   800 words. Slugged: BC-SPEEDING-WHILE SOBER-SLATE-NYTSF
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   2. WHAT'S BEHIND THE BRADLEY SURGE AND GORE STUMBLE? NOT MUCH,
by David Plotz
</P>
<P>
   The recent Bradley Surge and Gore Stumble have little to do with
the candidates. We are witnessing one of the first fake battles of
the campaign. This is the period when voters are indifferent, and
when journalists, Democratic candidates and Republican
troublemakers spin and position and jockey to write the script for
the coming real campaign.
</P>
<P>
   1,200 words. Slugged: BC-BRADLEY-PHONY-SURGE-SLATE-NYTSF
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   3. CLINTON RELOADS THE GUN CONTROL DEBATE, by William Saletan
</P>
<P>
   Bill Clinton's speech on gun control was a textbook illustration
of how to use a national trauma to reframe an issue. In the past,
he observed, rural Americans have thought of guns in terms of
hunting and the right to bear arms. In the future, Clinton wants
Americans to think of guns in new terms: bombs and kids.
</P>
<P>
   1,300 words. Slugged: BC-CLINTON-GUN-SPIN-SLATE-NYTSF
</P>
<P>
   -------
</P>
<P>
   4. SOME WEB RETAILERS HAVE TO SHED THEIR OFF-LINE WAYS, by James
Surowiecki
</P>
<P>
   In the off-line world, emulation is not the best route to
profitability. You have to differentiate yourself from your
competitors to create a real competitive advantage. But let's state
the obvious: Differentiation works only if you're different in a
better way. Companies like Toys R Us and Barnes &AMP; Noble should
visit their competitors' Web sites to see what works on-line and
what doesn't.
</P>
<P>
   800 words. Slugged: BC-OFF-LINE-RETAILERS-SLATE-NYTSF
</P>
<P>
   --------
</P>
<P>
   (Nonsubscribers to the Slate package: To publish any of these
articles, or other articles on the Slate
site--www.slate.com--contact New York Times Syndicate sales
representative DEBRA WEYDERT at 1-732-390-4480, or by fax at
732-390-4697.) &QL;
</P>
