<TEXT>
<P>
   CALIFORNIA-CAL-GUNS. Two weeks after the massacre at Columbine
High School, California's senators are taking a lead role in trying
to pass anti-gun legislation. While noting that passage remains
difficult, Democratic Sens. Barbara Boxers and Dianne Feinstein
said next week's vote on a juvenile justice bill offers the best
chance since Republicans took control of Congress in 1995. (500
words.) By Mark Stricherz
</P>
<P>
   COLORADO-LAND-PROTECT. The House Resources Committee unanimously
approved a bill Thursday that would give the government's strictest
environmental protection to 18,000 acres around the Spanish Peaks
southwest of Pueblo. (300 words.) By Charles Davant
</P>
<P>
   MAINE-REFUGEES-KOSOVO. The State Department politely declined
U.S. Sen. Susan M. Collins' offer to house Kosovar refugees at the
former Loring Air Force Base in Arostook County, but a few people
who fled the Balkan war still might come to Maine. (400 words.) By
Charles Davant
</P>
<P>
   MASSACHUSETTS-CAMPAIGN-FINANCE-MONEY. Rep. John Tierney,
D-Salem, introduced legislation today that would overhaul the
campaign finance system.(350 words.) By Mark D. Preston
</P>
<P>
   OHIO-MAYORS. As House Speaker Dennis Hastert began speaking to
local mayors Thursday, he remembered his connection to northeast
Ohio, Astabula County. Hastert has a good friend in the city of
Jefferson who he visits every once in a while. (300 words.) By Sean
Gorman
</P>
<P>
   WISCONSIN-KOSOVO-FUNDS. Repeating their vows to save Social
Security, at least three Wisconsin Republicans will vote against
the $12.9 billion funding bill for the military operations in
Kosovo because they say it contains extraneous costs that will
further sap the retirement trust fund. But LaCrosse Democrat Ron
Kind said the death of his constituent, Army Officer Kevin
Reichert, illustrates the need to make sure the military has enough
funds to minimize the risks faced by American troops, although he
disagrees with some of the non-emergency additions to the bill.
(500 words.) By Elizabeth Hurt
</P>
<P>
   -30-
</P>
