<P>
   AOL-ATT _ Following Wednesday's developments in the AT&AMP;T
purchase, America Online, the largest online service will find it
harder to find a high speed cable connection for its 13 million
subscribers. What will Case and company do? (Katz, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   w/TIMEWARNER _ATLANTA _We look at the impact of the AT&AMP;T deal on
Time Warner. Main impact is that Time Warner will probably move to
buy back full control of its content from a partnerhsip with
MediaOne. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BANK-EXEC _ ATLANTA _Isaiah Tidwell will be named president of
Wachovia-Georgia. A 26-year veteran of the bank, Tidwell becomes
the second minority executive to head the Georgia division of a
major bank. Nationsbank also recently named a veteran minority
executive to head its Georgia operations. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   HONDA-BAMA _ BIRMINGHAM _ On site in Birmingham where Honda is
expected to officially announce it will build a plant in Alabama
and give details. (Ritzler, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   DELL-NASHVILLE _ AUSTIN, Texas _Dell Computer Corp. officials
this morning announced plans to build a plant near Nashville
International Airport where at least 3,000 workers will make
desktop computers. Mayor Phil Bredesen, who spearheaded the city's
negotiations with Dell, says the number of workers here could climb
to 10,000 if the company continues its spectacular growth.
(Mahoney, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   CARS-ENTERTAIN _ Oldsmobile's Silhouette Premiere edition comes
with an entertainment package that should keep the kids amused on
the longest road trips. Ford and Dodge, to a lesser extent, have
affinity marketing deals that put video games in the back seat or
provide free vacations at the destination. (Ritzler, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   CHURCHS _ ATLANTA _ Later this month, Atlanta-based Church's
Chicken plans to kickoff a program aimed at getting more women into
its franchising network and hopes the program will help the indutry
overall. The Churchs Professional Mentoring Program will be a
year-long program. According to Church's, only 10 percent of the
franchise talen pool contains female entrepreneurs - a dismal
showing. (Poole, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
