<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUSINESS </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, May 7, and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact Susan Leh at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   DELIVERY-EXPANSION (Los Angeles) _ Westwind Express has been
purchased by Consolidated Delivery &AMP; Logistics, a much larger rival
headquartered in Clifton, N.J. Consolidated will make Westwind into
its West Coast operation. By Deborah Adamson.
</P>
<P>
   X X X &QL;
