<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Kansas City Star plans to move the following stories for use
by clients of the NYTimes News Service for AMs and PMs of Friday,
May 7. If you have any questions, please call Dennis Boone on the
Star's News Desk at (816) 234-4758.
</P>
<P>
   LEG07 _ A 6-year-old Wichita, Kan., girl will undergo a rare
surgery Friday at the University of Kansas Medical Center in Kansas
City. Cancer has destroyed the thigh bone in one of her legs.
Doctors will remove the cancerous part of her bone, amputate the
rest of her leg, turn it around 180 degrees and attach the
remaining thighbone to her hip. Her knee joint becomes her hip
joint, her ankle becomes her knee and she'll have a prosthetic
lower leg. And the doctor says she'll be able to play football and
wrestle, two sports she's really interested in. The little girl
also will be considered cancer-free once the surgery is done. By
Alan Bavley. Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   BANK06 _ An 18-year-old high school girl thought she was doing a
favor for a couple of friends by driving them to a recruiting
station Thursday. Along they way they stopped at a Gladstone bank.
One guy got back in the car and said drive _ fast. She did, only to
discover he'd just robbed the bank. She saw a cop, pulled over, and
jumped out of the car screaming for help. The FBI arrested the two
guys and she's been released as an innocent pawn. By Shawna Hamel.
Story will move in the ``a'' category.
</P>
<P>
   FARMLAND _ Farmland Industries and Cenex of St. Paul ahve signed
a tentative agreement to merge, in a move that would double the
size of what is already the biggest U.S. agricultural cooperative.
By Eric Palmer. Story will move in the ``f'' category.
</P>
<P>
   WESTERN _ The staff of the Kansas Corporation Commission, the
state's utility regulation board, approves the merger of
Topeka-based Western Resources and Kansas City Power &AMP; Light Co.,
throwing in a rate-reduction for customers. Story will move in the
``f'' category.
</P>
<P>
   AMCENT _ A consortium that includes American Century acquires
majority interest in an electronic stock exchange in the United
Kingdom. By Charles R.T. Crumply. Story will move in the ``f''
category.
</P>
<P>
   ATWORK-COLUMN ( ) _ Workplace column by DIANE STAFFORD. Story
will move in the ``f'' category.
</P>
