 &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; FOR PAGE A1 &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; TOLL  &LR; _ Today is a significant day for California consumers who
have been looking for ways to get a cheaper phone bill. That's
because customers can now choose any telecommunications provider as
their local toll carrier and will no longer be required to use
Pacific Bell. Local toll calls are calls made to regional numbers
that are more than 12 miles away, but are not considered
long-distance. But don't pick up the phone just yet.
</P>
<P>
   While the prices being offered by alternate carriers are
competitive, not everybody is a candidate for switching their local
toll provider. By Deborah Solomon
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; WORKPLACE &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR;  &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; KAISER _ &LR;  Kaiser's partnership with its unions was hailed as a
model of labor-management cooperation in the HMO industry when it
was launched in 1995. For the most part, the partnership has lived
up to its billing: It has expedited the startup of two hospitals,
cut the waiting time at pharmacies and helped one union organize
more quickly. By Tom Abate
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WORKWAYS _ &LR;  Ilana DeBare's Q&AMP;A workplace column.
</P>
