<P>
   FILM-MUMMY (Undated) _ Universal Pictures' remake of ``The
Mummy'' has morphed into an overblown, special-effects-o-rama
comedy that's closer in spirit to ``Abbott and Costello Meet the
Mummy'' than to the critically acclaimed horror movie from the
'30s.
</P>
<P>
   By William Arnold. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FILM-ELECTION (Undated) _ As directed by Alexander Payne,
``Election,'' which opens this weekend, is mostly funny. Matthew
Broderick as teacher Jim McAlister, gives a wonderfully deadpan and
long-suffering performance, much of it is very cleverly written and
staged, and its off-beat structure (with narration from all four
principal characters) somehow gives a brilliant cross-section of
the particular horror that is high-school life.
