<P>
   MUSIC-DIDDLEY (Seattle) _ Despite the fans he has made and the
awards he has won as one of the pioneers of rock 'n' roll, Bo
Diddley feels like a two-time loser. In the 1950s, '60s and '70s,
it was unscrupulous lawyers, agents and label executives that
conned him out of money he was rightly owed from the sales of his
records. Today, it's bootleggers, pirates and the Internet that are
depriving him of a better living.
</P>
