A7417 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-HAWKS07-COX     05-06 0338
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-HAWKS07-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Crawford draws tough assignment
 &HT;    By Jeffrey Denberg
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Chris Crawford was a second-round draft pick, 51st out
of 58 players taken in the 1997 draft. He came to Atlanta hoping to
earn enough money to someday open a sports bar back home in
Michigan.
</P>
<P>
   Turns out, years from now when Crawford retires, he will not
only have the money, he will be the guy the customers want to talk
about.
</P>
<P>
   ``See the big guy down there? Curly hair, getting a little
paunchy? He once guarded Grant Hill in the NBA playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   ``No kiddin'. How'd he do?''
</P>
<P>
   The response had better be ``held his own'' or ``pretty good,''
if the Hawks are going to knock out the Detroit Pistons in their
first-round series that starts Saturday night at the Georgia Dome.
</P>
<P>
   An unimposing veteran of 82 games over two seasons, owner of an
undistinguished 6.9 average, Crawford would celebrate his 24th
birthday next week. But he won't have time. Grant Hill will see to
that.
</P>
<P>
   Lenny Wilkens is aware of the task Crawford faces. ``The thing
is, he can't be intimidated,'' the coach said. ``Chris has played
well against Grant, so he can't allow the circumstance to overwhelm
him. And we have to help him.''
</P>
<P>
   Wilkens wants Crawford to keep Hill busy, so that Hill can't
cheat over and help double-team guard Steve Smith or slap the ball
away in the post. ``We can't let him roam,'' Wilkens said. ``Chris
has got to go hard, get up the floor, make Grant work. He's got to
contribute offensively, and he's got to stay away from cheap
fouls.''
</P>
<P>
   The flip side is that Wilkens doesn't want to commit Ty Corbin
to the small forward slot. He'd rather have Corbin ready to play
behind Crawford and shooting guard Steve Smith, but it can happen
only if Crawford makes a credible showing.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm very positive about this,'' said Crawford. ``I know (Hill)
is a great player, but I can do some things.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
