Cey Adams, designs album covers and Futura and Stash produce a
graffiti-inspired clothing line. At 37, Adams is the creative
director of Russell Simmons' Def Jam label. His work can be seen on
billboards advertising radio station Hot 97, WQHT (97.1), whose
fat, bold logo he designed, and on the album covers of countless
rappers, from L.L. Cool J. to E.p.m.D. (Jeffery A. Salter/New York
Times Photo) LITE
