 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-TAIWAN-POLITICS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 5)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 5,
about the softening of the call for formal independence from China
by the main opposition party on Taiwan misidentified the founder of
the governing Nationalist Party. It was Sun Yat-sen, not Chiang
Kai-shek.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MICROSOFT-ANTITRUST-NYT (moved on Monday, May 3)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 3,
about the lists of witnesses in the Microsoft antitrust trial
referred incorrectly to comments by Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson
about the earlier testimony of a witness, Richard Schmalensee of
the Sloan School of Management at the Massachusetts Institute of
Technology. The judge questioned an apparent contradiction in Mr.
Schmalensee's testimony; he did not question his overall
credibility.
</P>
