<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SYNCHRONIZED AND SHARING, LAKERS GET HOT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ When Mother's Day arrives this weekend, the
Lakers might want to thank mom for that old lesson about sharing.
It's possibly the key to their turnaround.
</P>
<P>
   Left for dead just a week and a half ago, the Los Angeles Lakers
closed out the season with four straight wins, three of them routs,
and are once again being talked about as contenders for the Western
Conference title. Their fortunes turned when they started sharing
the ball on offense and sharing responsibility on defense.
</P>
<P>
   For the season, the Lakers averaged 21 assists per game. But in
this winning streak, they've dished out 28 assists on average. The
same Lakers team tagged as a loose collection of me-first ball hogs
with personal agendas now makes more passes than Bill Clinton at a
NOW convention.
</P>
<P>
   A similar team approach on defense has keyed a run in which they
held the last four opponents to a combined 42.4 percent shooting.
</P>
<P>
   And all of that emerged from the Lakers' soul-cleansing team
meeting last week.
</P>
<P>
   ``The players have come together,'' coach Kurt Rambis said.
``They stressed to each other areas which we have to improve. They
got rid of all their little issues....
</P>
<P>
   ``It's easy for everybody to go out there and do what they want
to do.... The hard part is getting individuals to make sacrifices
of the things they like to do and pick up in the areas they don't
like to do for the benefit of the team, whether that's getting more
rebounds or passing the basketball more or playing better defense
individually or as a team.''
</P>
<P>
   So now Glen Rice, with 62 points in his past two games, is
clicking in the offense after previously looking lost among his new
teammates.
</P>
<P>
   And Derek Fisher, who only recently reclaimed the starting
point-guard job he'd lost, is averaging 7.3 assists and 8.0 points
in the last three games.
</P>
<P>
   And Robert Horry, a bit player buried on the bench for parts of
the season, scored a season-high 22 points against Portland last
week.
</P>
<P>
   And Rick Fox, battling injuries and role changes for much of the
season, is averaging 12 points in the last three games.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're hot, man, we're rolling,'' Kobe Bryant said.
``Everybody's involved, everybody's in sync. That's something that
Kurt has been stressing, wanting to get everyone involved, wanting
to get everybody a boost of confidence going into the playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   Even if leading scorers Bryant and Shaquille O'Neal have to give
up a few shots along the way to make it work.
</P>
<P>
   ``We just wanna win, that's all. I don't think it's a matter of
being selfish or unselfish,'' Bryant said. ``We just want to win
and we're going to do what it takes to win.''
</P>
<P>
   For the young Lakers, lessons are learned the hard way. They had
lost six of eight games, concluding with a 27-point loss at
Houston, before that team meeting. Maybe they had to bottom out in
order to find themselves.
</P>
<P>
   ``Yeah, I think so,'' Bryant said. ``We're a young team and
that's like your mother telling you to go outside and play, and you
have to fall on your face a couple times before you understand what
the hell she's talking about. That's what happened.''
</P>
<P>
   So thanks, mom.
</P>
<P>
   Two dimensional: Overshadowed in his 40-point outburst Wednesday
against Portland was Rice's solid defensive effort. Often
classified as a weak defender, Rice is among the Lakers who have
stepped up the defense during the recent winning streak.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's been giving a maximum defensive effort,'' Rambis said.
``I've been more impressed with his defense than anything he's done
offensively for us since he's been here. To me that's just an
indication that he's ready to move up and be a major, key
ballplayer for us.''
</P>
<P>
   Said Rice, ``I take a lot of pride in my defense. I hear a lot
of people saying, `Oh, Glen Rice can't play any defense.' I'm just
out to try to prove those guys wrong.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
